RACE.RACE_TEXT: Texas Arabian Derby - Grade3 RETAMA PARK RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 92. Stakes Purse 33000. FOR ARABIAN THREE AND FOUR YEARS OLD. No Nomination fee. Nominees to pay $250 to pass through the entry box and an additional $250 to start. Supplemental Nominations in the amount of $1,000 may be made at time of entry and shall include all fees. After p aying $1,000 for 6th through 12th place, the $30,000 Added from TABA HIEA Fund and all fees will to be divided 60% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 10% to third, 6% to fourth, 4% to fifth. Weight: Three Year olds 125 lbs. Four Year Olds 128 lbs. The field will be limited to (12) twelve horses. Highest career earnings at time of entry will be preferred. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usual time of closing. Horses not drawing a starting position in the gate will receive a refund of the entry fee. Winning owner to receive trophy.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WMA COUNTRY STAR dueled for the lead along the inside, kicked away from an outer foe after a right handed cue midway around the far turn, kept a clear advantage from around the two path into the stretch, and held sway. RB AFTERBURN had a slow start but was unhurried in the two path, was put to a ride into the far turn, had to steadly slightly midway around that turn, floated out to the five path into the stretch, and ran on for place. WMA GRAND FINALE was out in the six path around the first turn, vied for the lead in the two path down the backside, but lost ground around the far turn, and evened out for show. AA TAKE A CHANCE tracked in the five path but faded from the two path turning into the stretch. WMA BADGE dropped well off the pace and never menaced. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.
